Are any of you gentleman familiar with the ideas of Sigmund Freud? He was an Austrian neurologist of the 20th century who is the founder psychoanalysis (the study of the unconscious mind).  He had many ideas such as the Id, Ego, and Superego; defense mechanisms; psychosexual development of a child; psychological repression of memories; and contributed to the studies of dreams.  But what I will be talking about today is his idea of the Oedipus Complex, referring to the protagonist of Sophocles' famous tragedy, Oedipus Rex, who kills his father and marries his mother without knowing who she truly is.  The idea ties into Freud's stages of psychosexual development.  In stage 3 (typically from the ages of 3-6), the phallic stage, the boy learns the difference between the sexes and realizes that he has a penis while his mother does not.
